               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18191027-47-person517">
                  THOMAS 
                  HARPER
               <interp inst="t18191027-47-person517" type="surname" value="HARPER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191027-47-person517" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191027-47-person517" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Cowper's-court, Cornhill. On the 12th of October, about a quarter after twelve o'clock in the day, I was in <placeName id="t18191027-47-crimeloc265">Lower Thames-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18191027-47-crimeloc265" type="placeName" value="Lower Thames-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18191027-47-crimeloc265" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18191027-47-off263 t18191027-47-crimeloc265"></join>, and felt myself hustled by two boys bigger than the prisoner, one on each side - the prisoner was behind them. As soon as I turned round, the other two ran down Botolph wharf. I found the prisoner with my handkerchief in his hand, secured him, and gave him in custody at the Mansion House.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. There was a parcel of boys before me; the gentleman turned round, and they ran away. He<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181910270026"></xptr>struck me, and said,</p>
               <p>"Look at the handkerchief at your feet." He did not take it out of my hand.</p>
               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18191027-47-person518">
                  THOMAS 
                  HARPER
               <interp inst="t18191027-47-person518" type="surname" value="HARPER"></interp>
